    <script type="text/javascript">
        $(document).ready(function() {
            const ori_total = parseInt($('#section4').data('total'));
            let slider_loop = ori_total >= 3 ? true : false;
            $('#section4').Slider({
                slides: '.record-item',
                maxSlide: 1,
                swipeControl: true,
                skipBoundary: true,
                infiniteLoop: slider_loop,
                dummySlide: slider_loop,
				afterSlide: function(slider, slides, current_page, total_page) {
					if(slider_loop) {
						if(current_page == ori_total) {
							slider.Slider('jump', ori_total * 2).Slider('start');
						}
						if(current_page == ori_total * 2 + 1) {
							slider.Slider('jump', ori_total + 1).Slider('start');
						}
					}
				},
                afterInit: function(slider, slides, current_page, total_page) {
                    if(slider_loop) {
                        slider.Slider('jump', ori_total * 2);
                    }
                    else {
                        slider.Slider('jump', total_page);
                    }
                }
            });
        });
    </script>
</section>
<section id="section7" data-total="10">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
            <h2 class="colour2">What's New at CWBS?</h2>
            <span class="bg-colour1"></span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="record-slider">
        <div class="slider-container">
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="194">
                        <time>21/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>It’s been an action-packed stretch for CWBS sports! From Discovery Bay to Pok Fu Lam and Tai Po, our student-athletes have been out in full force, showing remarkable grit and sportsmanship across three sports events. At the HKPSSA Cross-Country Championships in Discovery Bay, our runners battled fierce competition and warm conditions to smash their personal bests, and that momentum carried right into the Tai Po Cross-Country Festival. We are so proud to celebrate our top finishers: Ho Lam took 1st place, followed by Leonard in 2nd, Charles in 3rd, and Spencer in 5th. Huge congratulations also go to Sophia, Amber, and Antoine for their outstanding top-5 finishes!<br><br>The energy continued at the HKPSSA Tag Rugby Championships at Stanley Ho Sports Ground, where CWBS stood out as the only school to field three full squads. Our Boys A team finished the day unbeaten, while our Boys B team made fantastic progress and our Girls team earned a well-deserved 3rd place finish in their group.<br><br>A massive thank you to Mr Gay, Mr Williams, and Mr Pattison for their dedication to the teams throughout the ECA program. Finally, a huge shout-out to the families who made the long trips to Lantau, Tai Po, and Pok Fu Lam, having you there on the sidelines to cheer means the world to our young athletes! Go CWBS!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/eb94fab3ca2aadee9636b4427b8e1d9a.jpg" alt="653576747_1257654429840482_3390493531286115403_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="193">
                        <time>20/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Last Friday, our school turned into a living storybook for Book Character Day!  The playground and classrooms were full of creativity as students and staff dressed in amazing outfits inspired by their favorite stories. We held a Character Catwalk where students had a chance to feature their unique costumes and share their characters with the whole school. It was such a fun way to celebrate reading and bring our favorite books to life!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/4d91ab7a7389d5e4ce1815c14eb6fbf7.jpg" alt="652933420_1256620556610536_4719515063792898824_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="192">
                        <time>11/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Huge congratulations to our Chinese BOB (Battle of the Books) team for or claiming the championship title today!<br><br>Competing against 7 other ESF schools, our students showed incredible grit and knowledge. After months of studying two books and tackling a series of questions, they secured the win in an extremely close and hard-fought final.<br><br>We celebrate their remarkable focus and passion for literature. Thank you, Ms Wu and Ms Li for leading the team and our parent volunteers for supporting today. Well done, team!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/2fcd835e5c6d3581d104d74f62859e46.jpg" alt="649274440_1249557067316885_5361375348429509371_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="191">
                        <time>10/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Book Week has officially arrived, and something truly extraordinary has taken root in our school. If you wander quietly enough, you might just find our very own Magic Tree - a whimsical sight reminiscent of the one found in Enid Blyton’s The Faraway Tree.<br><br>This isn’t just any tree, it’s a gateway to other worlds. Our students have been busy exploring with every sense engaged, while our Year 1 explorers have written letters to the folk living deep within. <br><br>The wonder doesn't stop at this magical creation, as there are plenty of ways to bring a new story home this week. Our Book Fair is open today and tomorrow for those looking for a brand-new adventure, followed by our Second-Hand Book Sale this Thursday to find a pre-loved treasure. Finally, we are all looking forward to the Book Character Parade this Friday, where our students will bring the school to life as their favourite characters!<br><br>It’s going to be a week full of wonder, imagination, and the joy of getting lost in a story. ✨</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/2f3177659c12a8dcb6eec7dd3ceca9e5.jpg" alt="649624893_1248852287387363_9076885066158483145_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="190">
                        <time>06/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our Year 4 students had a brilliant time on their camp this week! With perfect weather on our side, they jumped straight into kayaking, hiking, and team activities with incredible energy. A major highlight was watching their engineering skills in action as they built and tested their very own catapults.<br><br>It was a fantastic learning experience focused on teamwork and resilience. We are so proud of how every student participated and making the most of every moment.!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/1e8640ee319439a6f8c5c1523ecf5e8a.jpg" alt="648520299_1245820521023873_1069647308364247755_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="189">
                        <time>27/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>It has been a productive week of real-world learning as our Year 3 and Year 5 students took their inquiries beyond the classroom and into the vibrant streets and kitchens of our community.<br><br>As part of their How We Organise Ourselves unit, our Year 3 chefs traded their notebooks for aprons this week. To better understand food production and systems, the students visited a local pizzeria to see a professional production line in action. From stretching the dough to the placement of toppings, they learned that making the perfect pizza isn't just delicious, it’s a masterclass in efficiency and organisation.<br><br>Meanwhile, Year 5 hit the pavement in Causeway Bay for their How We Express Ourselves unit. Their mission was to investigate the central idea that media can shape thinking and behavior. During their Media Walk, the children immersed themselves in the practical world of advertising to apply their newly acquired knowledge. They sharpened their critical thinking skills by focusing on different adverts and their purposes, while also identifying various pricing strategies like bundling and charm pricing in a real-world context.<br><br>It is wonderful to see our students applying their classroom knowledge to the world around them. Thank you once again to our parent volunteers who kindly gave their time to support these trips.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/e9ab889a5f4f51ad8362f80967266d83.jpg" alt="644486598_1240460631559862_3419264757406318048_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="188">
                        <time>12/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>The CWBS community came together yesterday for our most spectacular event of the year, the annual Chinese New Year Assembly. The celebration kicked off with a powerful Chinese Drumming performance followed by a double Dragon Dance that featured both a traditional dragon brought to life by our staff and a magnificent woven dragon handcrafted and performed by our own students. Our Guzheng ensemble, choirs, and orchestra captured the festive spirit through a beautiful program of music, poetry, and dance that showcased the very best of our students' hard work and creativity. The Lion Dance also added an extra spark of excitement to the programme! <br><br>To wrap up the festivities, the entire school joined together for a  singalong of "Gong Xi Gong Xi." Following the assembly, the excitement continued as students participated in a rotation of cultural activities and traditional games across the school (thank you, parent volunteers!). If you missed the live show, the full recording of the event can be viewed on our Facebook page. We are so proud of everyone who made this celebration possible.<br><br>Wishing all families health and prosperity in the Year of the Horse!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/005c00c96bfd32e68a5826c6402cf1cb.jpg" alt="632271689_1227883776150881_872705526361758849_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="187">
                        <time>11/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>CWBS Lunar New Year celebrations</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/33c465f7bb01aedf8768ace7d3301b8f.jpg" alt="629152267_1244048607790433_1022871409153936204_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="186">
                        <time>11/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>CWBS Lunar New Year celebrations</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/9535f6ca145e3b4a68865e58ef053929.jpg" alt="631118307_893784710293583_3181051765894326556_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="185">
                        <time>05/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>Congratulations to our Year 1s for celebrating their 100 days at school and presenting their learning journey to their parents. The students were exceptional as they took the lead, guiding their families through the newfound skills and progress they have made in Language, Mathematics, Chinese, PE, and Expressive Arts since the start of the school year.<br><br>They also shared their proficiency with Learning Technology, illustrating just how much they have integrated these new tools into their daily discovery.<br><br>A big thank you to all the families who came along to see the children in action, it was a fantastic way to mark the milestone!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/3d36437ddf295345ae97f5e362093d86.jpg" alt="625463563_1221746430097949_865063011085273277_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="194">
                        <time>21/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>It’s been an action-packed stretch for CWBS sports! From Discovery Bay to Pok Fu Lam and Tai Po, our student-athletes have been out in full force, showing remarkable grit and sportsmanship across three sports events. At the HKPSSA Cross-Country Championships in Discovery Bay, our runners battled fierce competition and warm conditions to smash their personal bests, and that momentum carried right into the Tai Po Cross-Country Festival. We are so proud to celebrate our top finishers: Ho Lam took 1st place, followed by Leonard in 2nd, Charles in 3rd, and Spencer in 5th. Huge congratulations also go to Sophia, Amber, and Antoine for their outstanding top-5 finishes!<br><br>The energy continued at the HKPSSA Tag Rugby Championships at Stanley Ho Sports Ground, where CWBS stood out as the only school to field three full squads. Our Boys A team finished the day unbeaten, while our Boys B team made fantastic progress and our Girls team earned a well-deserved 3rd place finish in their group.<br><br>A massive thank you to Mr Gay, Mr Williams, and Mr Pattison for their dedication to the teams throughout the ECA program. Finally, a huge shout-out to the families who made the long trips to Lantau, Tai Po, and Pok Fu Lam, having you there on the sidelines to cheer means the world to our young athletes! Go CWBS!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/eb94fab3ca2aadee9636b4427b8e1d9a.jpg" alt="653576747_1257654429840482_3390493531286115403_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="193">
                        <time>20/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Last Friday, our school turned into a living storybook for Book Character Day!  The playground and classrooms were full of creativity as students and staff dressed in amazing outfits inspired by their favorite stories. We held a Character Catwalk where students had a chance to feature their unique costumes and share their characters with the whole school. It was such a fun way to celebrate reading and bring our favorite books to life!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/4d91ab7a7389d5e4ce1815c14eb6fbf7.jpg" alt="652933420_1256620556610536_4719515063792898824_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="192">
                        <time>11/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Huge congratulations to our Chinese BOB (Battle of the Books) team for or claiming the championship title today!<br><br>Competing against 7 other ESF schools, our students showed incredible grit and knowledge. After months of studying two books and tackling a series of questions, they secured the win in an extremely close and hard-fought final.<br><br>We celebrate their remarkable focus and passion for literature. Thank you, Ms Wu and Ms Li for leading the team and our parent volunteers for supporting today. Well done, team!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/2fcd835e5c6d3581d104d74f62859e46.jpg" alt="649274440_1249557067316885_5361375348429509371_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="191">
                        <time>10/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Book Week has officially arrived, and something truly extraordinary has taken root in our school. If you wander quietly enough, you might just find our very own Magic Tree - a whimsical sight reminiscent of the one found in Enid Blyton’s The Faraway Tree.<br><br>This isn’t just any tree, it’s a gateway to other worlds. Our students have been busy exploring with every sense engaged, while our Year 1 explorers have written letters to the folk living deep within. <br><br>The wonder doesn't stop at this magical creation, as there are plenty of ways to bring a new story home this week. Our Book Fair is open today and tomorrow for those looking for a brand-new adventure, followed by our Second-Hand Book Sale this Thursday to find a pre-loved treasure. Finally, we are all looking forward to the Book Character Parade this Friday, where our students will bring the school to life as their favourite characters!<br><br>It’s going to be a week full of wonder, imagination, and the joy of getting lost in a story. ✨</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/2f3177659c12a8dcb6eec7dd3ceca9e5.jpg" alt="649624893_1248852287387363_9076885066158483145_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="190">
                        <time>06/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Our Year 4 students had a brilliant time on their camp this week! With perfect weather on our side, they jumped straight into kayaking, hiking, and team activities with incredible energy. A major highlight was watching their engineering skills in action as they built and tested their very own catapults.<br><br>It was a fantastic learning experience focused on teamwork and resilience. We are so proud of how every student participated and making the most of every moment.!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/1e8640ee319439a6f8c5c1523ecf5e8a.jpg" alt="648520299_1245820521023873_1069647308364247755_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="189">
                        <time>27/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>It has been a productive week of real-world learning as our Year 3 and Year 5 students took their inquiries beyond the classroom and into the vibrant streets and kitchens of our community.<br><br>As part of their How We Organise Ourselves unit, our Year 3 chefs traded their notebooks for aprons this week. To better understand food production and systems, the students visited a local pizzeria to see a professional production line in action. From stretching the dough to the placement of toppings, they learned that making the perfect pizza isn't just delicious, it’s a masterclass in efficiency and organisation.<br><br>Meanwhile, Year 5 hit the pavement in Causeway Bay for their How We Express Ourselves unit. Their mission was to investigate the central idea that media can shape thinking and behavior. During their Media Walk, the children immersed themselves in the practical world of advertising to apply their newly acquired knowledge. They sharpened their critical thinking skills by focusing on different adverts and their purposes, while also identifying various pricing strategies like bundling and charm pricing in a real-world context.<br><br>It is wonderful to see our students applying their classroom knowledge to the world around them. Thank you once again to our parent volunteers who kindly gave their time to support these trips.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/e9ab889a5f4f51ad8362f80967266d83.jpg" alt="644486598_1240460631559862_3419264757406318048_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="188">
                        <time>12/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>The CWBS community came together yesterday for our most spectacular event of the year, the annual Chinese New Year Assembly. The celebration kicked off with a powerful Chinese Drumming performance followed by a double Dragon Dance that featured both a traditional dragon brought to life by our staff and a magnificent woven dragon handcrafted and performed by our own students. Our Guzheng ensemble, choirs, and orchestra captured the festive spirit through a beautiful program of music, poetry, and dance that showcased the very best of our students' hard work and creativity. The Lion Dance also added an extra spark of excitement to the programme! <br><br>To wrap up the festivities, the entire school joined together for a  singalong of "Gong Xi Gong Xi." Following the assembly, the excitement continued as students participated in a rotation of cultural activities and traditional games across the school (thank you, parent volunteers!). If you missed the live show, the full recording of the event can be viewed on our Facebook page. We are so proud of everyone who made this celebration possible.<br><br>Wishing all families health and prosperity in the Year of the Horse!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/005c00c96bfd32e68a5826c6402cf1cb.jpg" alt="632271689_1227883776150881_872705526361758849_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="187">
                        <time>11/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>CWBS Lunar New Year celebrations</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/33c465f7bb01aedf8768ace7d3301b8f.jpg" alt="629152267_1244048607790433_1022871409153936204_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="186">
                        <time>11/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>CWBS Lunar New Year celebrations</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/9535f6ca145e3b4a68865e58ef053929.jpg" alt="631118307_893784710293583_3181051765894326556_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="185">
                        <time>05/02/2026</time>
                        <h3>Congratulations to our Year 1s for celebrating their 100 days at school and presenting their learning journey to their parents. The students were exceptional as they took the lead, guiding their families through the newfound skills and progress they have made in Language, Mathematics, Chinese, PE, and Expressive Arts since the start of the school year.<br><br>They also shared their proficiency with Learning Technology, illustrating just how much they have integrated these new tools into their daily discovery.<br><br>A big thank you to all the families who came along to see the children in action, it was a fantastic way to mark the milestone!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/3d36437ddf295345ae97f5e362093d86.jpg" alt="625463563_1221746430097949_865063011085273277_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="194">
                        <time>21/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>It’s been an action-packed stretch for CWBS sports! From Discovery Bay to Pok Fu Lam and Tai Po, our student-athletes have been out in full force, showing remarkable grit and sportsmanship across three sports events. At the HKPSSA Cross-Country Championships in Discovery Bay, our runners battled fierce competition and warm conditions to smash their personal bests, and that momentum carried right into the Tai Po Cross-Country Festival. We are so proud to celebrate our top finishers: Ho Lam took 1st place, followed by Leonard in 2nd, Charles in 3rd, and Spencer in 5th. Huge congratulations also go to Sophia, Amber, and Antoine for their outstanding top-5 finishes!<br><br>The energy continued at the HKPSSA Tag Rugby Championships at Stanley Ho Sports Ground, where CWBS stood out as the only school to field three full squads. Our Boys A team finished the day unbeaten, while our Boys B team made fantastic progress and our Girls team earned a well-deserved 3rd place finish in their group.<br><br>A massive thank you to Mr Gay, Mr Williams, and Mr Pattison for their dedication to the teams throughout the ECA program. Finally, a huge shout-out to the families who made the long trips to Lantau, Tai Po, and Pok Fu Lam, having you there on the sidelines to cheer means the world to our young athletes! Go CWBS!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/eb94fab3ca2aadee9636b4427b8e1d9a.jpg" alt="653576747_1257654429840482_3390493531286115403_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="193">
                        <time>20/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Last Friday, our school turned into a living storybook for Book Character Day!  The playground and classrooms were full of creativity as students and staff dressed in amazing outfits inspired by their favorite stories. We held a Character Catwalk where students had a chance to feature their unique costumes and share their characters with the whole school. It was such a fun way to celebrate reading and bring our favorite books to life!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/4d91ab7a7389d5e4ce1815c14eb6fbf7.jpg" alt="652933420_1256620556610536_4719515063792898824_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="192">
                        <time>11/03/2026</time>
                        <h3>Huge congratulations to our Chinese BOB (Battle of the Books) team for or claiming the championship title today!<br><br>Competing against 7 other ESF schools, our students showed incredible grit and knowledge. After months of studying two books and tackling a series of questions, they secured the win in an extremely close and hard-fought final.<br><br>We celebrate their remarkable focus and passion for literature. Thank you, Ms Wu and Ms Li for leading the team and our parent volunteers for supporting today. Well done, team!</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/2fcd835e5c6d3581d104d74f62859e46.jpg" alt="649274440_1249557067316885_5361375348429509371_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
